Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the directed information rate and its lower bound, which are fundamental concepts in information theory. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a likely category as the paper studies networked control systems and their closed-loop performance. 
3. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is a possible category as the paper deals with the communication between different components of the control system. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper studies networked control systems and their communication over digital channels. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the use of coding schemes to achieve the desired performance level.
